Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding the intention of an utterance. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper focuses on the acoustic features of speech. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for the task. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of different models. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with understanding the interaction between auditory and linguistic processes.
